 size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>11 - 13</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Skeleton Lrodd Room</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Not known</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Ward Undead, Darkness</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Skeleton Lrodd is the cheapest boss in befallen.  To solo him you need to be at least level 10.<br><br> 

Before you go into the Skeleton Lrodd's room, there will be 3 Skeleton and 1 wimp Skeleton at the center room.  You may Invisibility Versus Undead to go through them or simply clear them.  They spawn at low rate, around 10 mins.  Go through the center room and go into the right hand side second door, that is the skeleton Lrodd room.  Inside you see a corridor spawn 1 Giant Rat & 1 Skeleton, clear them.  Turn left and you see 1 more Skeleton and inside is the Skeleton Lrodd with 2 other Skeletons guarding him.<br><br>

Here you attack any 3 of them.  They probably come out together.  My strategy is to target Skeleton Lrodd and Darkness & pet attack.  Keep your pet tanking him & Ward Undead him like crazy (each take him 40hp).  If it cons yellow to you, probably he dies before your pet dies.  If your pet dies first, immediately turn around, open the door, and run to the hell zone.  The distance is short and you should escape with some HP.<br><br>

Note 1: You may use the pet guard here command and pull the Skeleton Lrodd outside, just in front of zone.  Just make sure you clear the road.<br><br>

Note 2: Be aware of the high level train such as Ice Boned Skeleton.  Watch out for the narration since he will speak and laugh before he appears.</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:buncage@hotmail.com'>Adaraa</td></tr><tr></table><br><br></table></div>